               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1289" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1289" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1289" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 32.) On the evening of the 7th of February, I was on duty in Lime-street, and met the prisoner, about half-past six o'clock, with a bundle of shovels on his back, in com<lb></lb>pany</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183902040190"></xptr>
               <p>with another lad—I went up to him, and his companion whistled—the prisoner then threw the shovels down, and ran away—I followed, and he was stopped without my losing sight of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1290" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1290" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1290" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1290" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN THOMPSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Thomas Kenning and William Chapman, of Philpot-lane and Birmingham. I missed two dozen shovels from their stock—I am certain these are our property—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were you always certain of them? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I do not believe I have said I believed them to be ours—(<hi rend="italic">The witness's deposition being read, stated, "I believe them to be part of those stolen"</hi>)—the person who wrote that should have put it in a different form—he read it over to me—I was certain of them before the Magistrate—all shovels that come from Birmingham are done up in the same way—we had twelve dozen looked up for an order—I know them by this mark on two, "J. L. &amp; Co.," meaning "John Linden &amp; Co."—they are extensive manufacturers at Birmingham—there was a tally on them when taken, si<lb></lb>milar to what I have here.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
